        android:padding="2dp"
        android:text="Coconut is a tropical crop and grows well a hot climate. The coconut thrives well within 23 degrees of the equator (Between 200N and 200S latitudes) and an altitude of up to 600 m above Mean Sea Level. However, it is being grown up to 900 m above mean sea level in some places. The temperature should be from 20 ° to 32°C.  High temperature may cause the developing inflorescence to dry up, and limit production during those months in the year. "
        android:textColor="#000000" />

    <Button
